Artwork: the ukiyo-e prints are public domain (Eisen d. 1848, Hiroshige
d. 1858, Hokusai d. 1849). Scan provenance for the 69 station prints is
recorded per-station in data/stations.json; the overworld map is recorded in
assets/sources.json. The overworld scan (Hokusai, "Kisoji meisho ichiran",
Kobe City Museum) is licensed CC BY-ND 4.0 and is used unmodified, resized
only.

Music: the three bundled tracks are third-party works under licences that
permit redistribution — CC BY 4.0 and CC0. They are not covered by the MIT
licence above, and CC BY obliges you to keep their attribution: see
game-assets/bgm/CREDITS.md, which travels with the files. (A fourth piece of
music, the 8-bit walking theme, is synthesised in-browser with the Web Audio
API and is part of the source code.)

Font: the embedded subset of Yuji Boku is licensed under the SIL Open Font
License 1.1 — see game-assets/fonts/OFL.txt.

